        "description": "Typical for pulsed cleaning; higher rates increase speed but risk heat accumulation on low-conductivity Lanthanum. 30 kHz balances efficiency and safety. Trade-off: >50 kHz may cause overheating. Source: Academic literature, e.g., J. Laser Appl. (2021) on repetition rate effects in metal surface prep."
